SHORT TAKES; 
PAULEY'S 'TODAY' TO END DEC. 29 
Jane Pauley will wind up her long-running stint on NBC's "Today" on Dec. 29. A 
retrospective of her 13 years on the show will air during the 8:30 to 9 a.m. 
segment that morning. Her successor, Deborah Norville, won't take over until 
Jan. 8. In the interim, co-anchor Bryant Gumbel will be joined by four hosts 
from "Today Shows Past," including John Chancellor, Jan. 2; Hugh Downs, Jan. 3; 
Joe Garagiola, Jan. 4, and Tom Brokaw, Jan. 5. 
